{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8f31f9d-c558-42b8-be42-b558b4daca9e","content":"Here's the current state: a minimal .NET 10 Web API with two small markdown docs and no dependencies beyond the SDK. Here's my proposed architecture:\n\n---\n\n## RAG Q&A Architecture Plan\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   .NET 10 Web API                    │\n├──────────────┬──────────────────┬───────────────────┤\n│  Ingestion   │   Vector Store   │   Query Endpoint  │\n│  Service     │   (in-memory)    │   /api/ask        │\n├──────────────┼──────────────────┼───────────────────┤\n│ • Read .md   │ • Store chunks + │ • Embed question  │\n│ • Chunk text │   embeddings     │ • Similarity search│\n│ • Embed via  │ • Cosine sim     │ • Build prompt w/ │\n│   OpenAI API │   search         │   top-K context   │\n│              │                  │ • Call LLM → answer│\n└──────────────┴──────────────────┴───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1. Document Ingestion Pipeline\n- **Loader** — reads all `*.md` files from `Docs/` at startup (+ optional re-index endpoint `POST /api/ingest`)\n- **Chunker** — splits markdown by heading sections, then applies a sliding-window strategy (e.g. 512 tokens, 64-token overlap) to keep chunks small enough for embedding models\n- **Embedder** — calls OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` or `Azure.AI.OpenAI`) to produce vectors per chunk\n\n### 2. Vector Store\n- **In-memory store** using a simple `List<DocumentChunk>` with cosine-similarity search (sufficient for a small doc set)\n- Each entry: `{ Id, SourceFile, HeadingPath, Text, float[] Embedding }`\n- Could later swap for a persistent store (Qdrant, Azure AI Search, pgvector)\n\n### 3. Query Endpoint (`POST /api/ask`)\n- Request: `{ \"question\": \"How do I install?\" }`\n- Steps: embed question → retrieve top-K chunks (K=3–5) → construct grounded prompt → call LLM → return answer + source references\n- Response: `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [\"getting-started.md § Getting Started\"] }`\n\n### 4. Packages Needed\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` | Unified AI abstractions (embeddings + chat) |\n| `Markdig` | Parse markdown for heading-aware chunking |\n\n### 5. Configuration\n- `appsettings.json` section for OpenAI API key, model names, chunk size, overlap, top-K\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n- **Heading-aware chunking** so chunks respect document structure rather than splitting mid-sentence\n- **In-memory vector store** keeps things simple for a small corpus; abstracted behind an interface for future swap\n- **Microsoft.Extensions.AI** as the abstraction layer so the LLM provider (OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, local) is swappable\n- **Source attribution** returned with every answer for traceability\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to implement this, or would you like to adjust the approach first (e.g., different vector store, different embedding provider, chunk strategy)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57281d90-0d73-4c3a-b562-33c4b10ed66f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a good understanding of the current state. Let me create a plan for the RAG-based Q&A feature. The project is a minimal .NET 10 Web API with some markdown docs. I'll create a comprehensive architectural plan.","outputTokens":917,"requestId":"2C04:22188A:185CFB8:1B86E1A:69FD4574"},"id":"1855768d-ff86-4a36-959c-373a4e2e1640","timestamp":"2026-05-08T02:08:09.289Z","parentId":"704a75f8-d71e-49ec-8ecd-4af0a5152cc6"}
